cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the security risks and vulnerabilities in package managers, which are related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper proposes a framework for analyzing package managers, which involves programming languages (cs.PL) and system and information security (cs.SI). The paper also proposes a vetting pipeline for detecting malware in packages, which involves distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
